FBIS4-40634 "drsov118_d_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-118 Daily Report 19 Jun 1994 Regional Affairs Deputy Interior Minister Visits N. Ossetia, Ingushetia Deputy Interior Minister Visits N. Ossetia, Ingushetia LD1906090394 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0630 GMT 19 Jun 94 LD1906090394 Moscow 2x2 Television Russian BFN [Text] Yevgeniy Abramov, first deputy interior minister of the Russian Federation, completed a three-day working visit to North Ossetia and Ingushetia on 18 June. A correspondent from the POSTFAKTUM news agency learned at the Russian Interior Ministry's public relations center that Militia Colonel General Abramov met with North Ossetian President Galazov, Ingush President Aushev, and [Aleksandr] Lozovoy, chief of the interim administration in the area of the state of emergency. During the meeting, they planned a package of specific measures to raise the efficiency of the work of the internal affairs bodies in the rayons.
